ed rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is orchestration/state-handoff logic across modules (image result + text result + decision + publish/hold path), so Unit is too low (MOCK-MISS). It can be verified with deterministic safe results from both checks; no need for real model-output quality judgment. SUB-AGENTIC PROOF from behavior text: \"passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped\" describes plumbing of outcomes, not model accuracy. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no real OS/network/subprocess required; no agentic-quality assertion; no multi-agentic chain required.","test_description":"Wire moderation service, decision engine, and publish/hold repositories in-process. Force both checks to return PASS and assert final state is published exactly once, with no hold record and no dropped message.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is an end-to-end SLO over multiple real AI stages in sequence (image model call, text model call, then decision), so MULTI-STEP applies. Mocks can hide true latency composition and queueing effects (MOCK-HIDE). System alone was considered, but behavior explicitly covers the chained agentic pipeline; Workflow is the minimum boundary that captures sequence-level timing risk.","test_description":"Execute end-to-end submissions through the live moderation pipeline using real image/text model calls and measure submit-to-terminal-decision latency; assert p95 (or required percentile) is <=5s under peak-like load profile.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.27,"Workflow":0.5